iFor this problem to appear, all three requirements must be met:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i1. **`add paths yes;` option is turned on** , so that secondary routes		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   are sent to other nodes as well. If this option wasn't turned on,		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   as soon as the BuyVM node choose the VirMach node as the next hop,		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   it won't broadcast its route through Lutoma to the VirMach node.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   Then, the VirMach node will only have the option of sending traffic		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   directly to KSKB.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i2. Route preference algorithm **preferring secondary routes over		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   primary routes from other nodes** . Therefore, if we want to keep `add		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   paths yes;` option on, while designing the iBGP route preference		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   algorithm, we need to guarantee that routes from the same node **have		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   their priorities in the same order as that node** , so that the		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   primary routes will always be used over secondary routes.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i3. Routes passing Lutoma's network were incorrectly updated with the		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   new BGP community, causing the change of route priority orders.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
